Answer:
gpt_response:
The molecular formula of CCC1=CSC(=N1)CC(C)O can be determined by examining the chemical structure and identifying the individual elements present in the molecule. In this case, the molecule contains carbon (C), sulfur (S), nitrogen (N), and oxygen (O) atoms.

By counting the number of each atom in the molecular formula, we can determine the overall composition of the molecule. In this case, there are 9 carbon atoms, 2 sulfur atoms, 1 nitrogen atom, and 1 oxygen atom. Therefore, the molecular formula of the compound is C9H9NS2O.
